metadata.name: Antigravity #450
metadata.description:
To change size or quality, open the IPFS link in a separate window and append to its url a string like `&quality=400&tiles=9,16`. You may notice two parameters in it: `quality` and `tiles`.

`quality` is an integer from 1 to ~1000, the better the quality ‚Äî the slower the rendering. Default is 200.

`tiles` is a number of 256√ó256 px tiles to render. Can be an integer (for square images) or two integers separated with a¬†comma (for rectangular). `tiles=9,16` will make an image with width of 9√ó256 px = 2304 px and height of 16√ó256 px = 4096 px. If not set, adapts to screen size.

Press `s` to save the image.

metadata.name: Digital Monolith 160 #41
metadata.description:
This is my first monolith here on fxhash (and the first generative version of it too).

The artwork represents the exchange of digital data, like in networks or other electronic processes.

This is a collaboration with @andrew0 who wrote the code and created the music tracks (click to start audio if it doesn‚Äôt start automatically).

There are 4 sets of moving cubes, and a total of 16 different colors, plus 4 different core cubes and 7‚Äôdifferent backgrounds. 

Audio loops follow the different backgrounds, while percussive sounds follow the cubes cores.

All sounds are tuned to A to 432hz and are created using the Arturia library and Logic Pro DAW.

metadata.name: Freedom #39
metadata.description:
This art is fully generated, birds and barbed wire are drawing line by line.
Minted variation still contain some random parameters (birds strokes, barbed wire stroke, background noise). You can refresh page for get new small variation.
Each 15 token contains black sun.

Right click saving avaible in 1200x1200 resolution.

I dedicate this project to all people who are unjustly deprived of their freedom.
